Add OpenFire Instant Messaging in Mozilla Thunderbird
Launch Mozilla Thunderbird
Select File > New > Chat Account...
Select XMPP > Click Next
Input the OpenFire username and domain > Click Next
Input the chat user passwords > Click Next
Set the Local Alias field
From the Connection security dropdown, select Require encryption is SSL has been setup, otherwise select Use encryption if available
In the Server field enter the IP address or DNS name for the OpenFire server
Click Next
Click Fini 
Enjoy instant messaging inside the Thunderbird e-mail client
